        <div class="action-box">
            <h3><span class="emoji">‚úÖ</span> What You Need to Do When Approaching ‚Çπ20 Lakhs</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Watch Your Income:</strong> Track when combined rent reaches ‚Çπ19-20 Lakhs</li>
                <li><strong>Prepare Documents:</strong> Gather rent agreements and property details</li>
                <li><strong>Meet Your CA:</strong> Consult 2-3 months before hitting ‚Çπ20 Lakhs</li>
                <li><strong>Plan Registration:</strong> You have 30 days from crossing ‚Çπ20 Lakhs to register</li>
                <li><strong>Notify Tenants:</strong> Tell commercial tenant about GST/FCM changes after registration</li>
                <li><strong>Set Up System:</strong> Prepare to issue GST invoices and track TDS deductions</li>
                <li><strong>Arrange Filing:</strong> Set up monthly/quarterly GST return filing with CA</li>
                <li><strong>Plan Cash Flow:</strong> Account for TDS 10% deduction on all rent payments</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="grid" style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
            <div class="card">
                <h2><span class="emoji">‚ùì</span> Common Questions</h2>
                
                <h3>Q: Will my residential rent increase?</h3>
                <p><strong>A:</strong> No. Company keeps handling GST under RCM. No change for you.</p>
                
                <h3>Q: Who pays GST on commercial after I register?</h3>
                <p><strong>A:</strong> YOU must collect 18% GST and pay to government (FCM).</p>
                
                <h3>Q: What is TDS @ 10%?</h3>
                <p><strong>A:</strong> Tenant deducts 10% from total rent. You receive less cash upfront. Applies when yearly rent exceeds ‚Çπ2.4L.</p>
                
                <h3>Q: Can I delay registration?</h3>
                <p><strong>A:</strong> No. MUST register within 30 days. Penalties apply for late registration.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2><span class="emoji">üí°</span> Important Reminders</h2>
                
                <p style="background: #E3F2FD; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 15px;"><strong>üìå Remember:</strong> The ‚Çπ20 Lakh limit includes ALL rental income (both properties combined).</p>
                
                <p style="background: #E8F5E9; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 15px;"><strong>üìå Residential:</strong> Company continues RCM (no change for you).</p>
                
                <p style="background: #FFF3E0; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px;"><strong>üìå Commercial:</strong> You'll collect GST after registration (FCM - latest rule).</p>
            </div>
